## 4. CRITICAL RISKS

### 🔴 RISK 1 — [assignAdmin](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.controller.js#557-647) membership check is a no-op (Logic Bug)

**File:** [channel.controller.js](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.controller.js) line 584–588

```js
const _isTargetMember = isMember(channel.members, targetUserId); // result stored in prefixed var

if (!isMember) {  // ← checking the *function reference* isMember, not the boolean result
  return res.status(400).json({ message: "User is not a member of this channel" });
}
```

The `_isTargetMember` variable (ESLint-prefixed to suppress unused-var warnings) is declared but never evaluated. The condition `!isMember` checks the truthiness of the imported [isMember](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.model.js#58-68) *function* (always truthy), so **the membership guard never fires**. Any admin can promote any user ID — even one who is not a channel member — to admin.

---

### 🔴 RISK 2 — [removeChannelMember](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.controller.js#270-304) (legacy endpoint) uses wrong member filter format

**File:** [channel.controller.js](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.controller.js) line 289

```js
channel.members = channel.members.filter((m) => String(m) !== String(victimId));
```

Members are stored as `{ user: ObjectId, joinedAt: Date }` objects. `String(m)` on an object returns `[object Object]`, which will never equal a user ID string. The filter becomes a no-op — **the member is never removed**. The function reports success and emits socket events, but the member remains.

Note: This is in [removeChannelMember](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.controller.js#270-304) (DELETE `/member`). The newer [removeMember](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.controller.js#929-1037) (POST `/remove-member`) correctly handles the nested format. Both routes are registered, creating a silent failure path.

---

### 🔴 RISK 3 — Dual socket room naming creates guaranteed real-time delivery failures

**Controller emissions** use `channel_${id}` format (underscore):
```js
io.to(`channel_${channelId}`).emit(...)   // channel.controller.js — all emissions
io.to(`channel_${originalMsg.channel}`).emit(...)  // message.controller.js AI reply
```

**Socket handler room joins** use `channel:${id}` format (colon):
```js
socket.join(`channel:${channelId}`)       // messages.socket.js lines 43, 113
```

These are **different rooms**. Clients join `channel:<id>` rooms. Server emits to `channel_<id>` rooms. **No channel-scoped real-time event (member-added, member-removed, channel-updated, channel-deleted, tab events) is delivered to any connected client.**

The only events that work are those emitted to `workspace_<id>` or direct `user_<id>` rooms.

---

### 🟠 RISK 4 — [getMyChannels](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/client/src/services/channelService.js#5-7) returns member arrays for all channels to a non-member

**File:** [channel.controller.js](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.controller.js) lines 142–156

The query uses `$or` to return discoverable public channels to everyone. This means a non-member receives the full document including `members[]` array (with user ObjectIds, join dates) for all public channels. The response includes `channel.members` without stripping sensitive sub-fields.

---

### 🟠 RISK 5 — [updateChannel](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/client/src/services/channelService.js#17-19) (PUT [/:id](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/middleware/validate.js#8-36)) emits to `io.emit(...)` — broadcasts globally

**File:** [channel.controller.js](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.controller.js) line 397

```js
if (io) io.emit("channel-updated", payload);
```

`io.emit` (no room specified) broadcasts to **every connected socket on the server**. Every user on any workspace receives `channel-updated` events for every channel modification.

---

### 🟠 RISK 6 — [joinChannelViaLink](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.controller.js#1165-1270) does not validate channel privacy

**File:** [channel.controller.js](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.controller.js) lines 1169–1268

[joinChannelViaLink](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.controller.js#1165-1270) checks workspace membership but does **not** check `channel.isPrivate`. A user can join a private channel by directly calling `POST /:id/join-via-link` if they are a workspace member. There is no `if (channel.isPrivate) return 403` guard in this path.

---

### 🟠 RISK 7 — Message text is not sanitized before storage

**Files:** [message.controller.js](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/messages/message.controller.js) (sendChannelMessage), [messages.routes.js](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/messages/messages.routes.js) (sendChannelMessage)

Message `text` is stored as-is. There is no HTML sanitization (e.g., DOMPurify server-side) before persistence. If the frontend renders message text as `innerHTML` anywhere, stored `<script>` tags or event handler attributes constitute a stored XSS vector.

---

## 5. STRUCTURAL GAPS

| Gap | Location |
|---|---|
| No service layer between controller and model | [channel.controller.js](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.controller.js) handles all business logic inline |
| Two parallel message route stacks coexist | `/api/messages/*` (legacy) and `/api/v2/messages/*` (modular) both active |
| [channel.model.js](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.model.js) has no soft-delete field | No `deletedAt` or `isDeleted` flag; deletion is permanent and cascades to all messages immediately |
| [message.model.js](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/messages/message.model.js) has duplicate thread parent fields | `threadParent` and `parentId` both exist (line 33–34) and serve the same purpose |
| Tab canvas content stored as raw string in channel document | Unbounded `content: String` and `drawingData: Array` on embedded tab subdocuments; large collaborations will bloat the channel document |
| No channel name uniqueness constraint per workspace | `ChannelSchema.index({ workspace: 1, name: 1 })` is defined but `unique: true` is missing; two channels with identical names can coexist in the same workspace |
| `messageCount` field on channel schema is never incremented | The field exists but no controller ever calls `channel.messageCount++`. It is always 0. |
| `lastMessageAt` on channel is never updated by channel messages | Only [sendChannelMessage](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/messages/message.controller.js#70-109) in the old controller creates messages; it does not update `channel.lastMessageAt`. |
| File uploads return relative paths | Upload handler returns `url: /uploads/${file.filename}`; no base URL is prepended. This is only resolvable as a relative path on the same origin. |
| No validation schema on channel routes | [channel.routes.js](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.routes.js) uses no `express-validator` chains; the [validate](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/middleware/validate.js#8-36) middleware from [validate.js](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/middleware/validate.js) is never applied to any channel endpoint |

---

## 6. SECURITY RISKS

| Severity | Finding |
|---|---|
| 🔴 HIGH | [assignAdmin](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.controller.js#557-647) membership guard is a no-op (Bug Risk 1) — any admin can promote arbitrary user IDs |
| 🔴 HIGH | [joinChannelViaLink](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.controller.js#1165-1270) does not reject private channels (Risk 6) |
| 🟠 MEDIUM | [getPublicChannels](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/client/src/services/channelService.js#11-13) returns cross-workspace channel data; no workspace scoping |
| 🟠 MEDIUM | [updateChannel](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/client/src/services/channelService.js#17-19) emits to all sockets globally (`io.emit`) leaking channel metadata |
| 🟠 MEDIUM | Message `text` and `description` fields are not HTML-sanitized before storage; XSS potential if rendered raw |
| 🟠 MEDIUM | File uploads accept any file type; `upload.array('files', 5)` has no MIME type restriction or virus scanning |
| 🟡 LOW | [getChannelDetails](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/channels/channel.controller.js#703-754) membership check returns `403` but exposes the error message "You are not a member of this channel" — confirms channel existence to non-members |
| 🟡 LOW | Job: channel name is forced lowercase on update (`name.trim().toLowerCase()`) but NOT on creation — inconsistent normalization could allow duplicate lookups |
| 🟡 LOW | `socket.user = { id: decoded.sub }` — socket auth stores only user ID; no workspace/role context validated at socket layer |
| 🟡 LOW | [operationRateLimit](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/middleware/validate.js#95-139) custom in-memory limiter resets on redeploy and does not work in multi-instance deployments |

