## 7. SCALABILITY RISKS

| Risk | Detail |
|---|---|
| **N+1 queries per message** | [getChannelMessages](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/messages/message.controller.js#170-314) fires 2 queries per message (reply count + avatars) + 1 per member. 50 messages in a 30-member channel = ~150 extra queries per page load. |
| **Unbounded member list in [getChannelMembers](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/client/src/services/channelService.js#29-31)** | No pagination; entire members array is populated and returned in one response. Channels with 1,000+ members will be slow. |
| **Tab content in channel document** | Canvas `drawingData: Array` and `content: String` are embedded subdocuments. A heavily-used canvas tab bloats the channel document, slowing every fetch that includes the channel document. |
| **30-second unconditional polling in [ChannelsPanel](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/client/src/components/layout/panels/ChannelsPanel.jsx#11-516)** | Every active user fires an HTTP GET every 30 seconds regardless of WebSocket state. At scale, this generates constant background load. |
| **`messageCount` is never maintained** | If used for sorting or display, it will always show 0 and require a full `count()` query to compute correctly. |
| **No index on `channel.isDiscoverable`** | Discoverable-channel queries (`{ isPrivate: false, isDiscoverable: true }`) in [getMyChannels](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/client/src/services/channelService.js#5-7) are not covered by any index beyond the workspace-level compound index. |
| **Message query uses `createdAt` range without compound index** | [getChannelMessages](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/server/src/features/messages/message.controller.js#170-314) filters `{ channel, threadParent: null, createdAt: { $gte } }`. The index `{ channel: 1, _id: 1 }` exists but `threadParent` and `createdAt` filters are not in the indexed fields — COLLSCAN on the filtered sub-set. |

---

## 8. UI/UX GAPS

| Gap | Detail |
|---|---|
| **No unread count on channel list items** | [ChannelsPanel](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/client/src/components/layout/panels/ChannelsPanel.jsx#11-516) renders channel items with no badge/indicator for unread messages |
| **No optimistic UI on channel creation** | `useChannels.createChannel` adds the item locally, but [ChannelsPanel](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/client/src/components/layout/panels/ChannelsPanel.jsx#11-516) does a full refetch instead, causing a visible flash |
| **Discoverable channels in sidebar show as joinable but clicking navigates** | Non-member discoverable channels show a `UserPlus` icon but [handleClick](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/client/src/components/layout/panels/ChannelsPanel.jsx#280-301) calls `navigate(item.path)` — there is no join prompt on click |
| **[Item](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/client/src/components/layout/panels/ChannelsPanel.jsx#277-361) component defined inside parent** | Re-renders entire list of channel items on any parent state change (search input, selection mode, modal open) |
| **Channel search is client-side only** — filters already-loaded channels; no server-side search endpoint for channels | |
| **No loading skeleton** | Loading state shows plain text "Loading channels..." with no skeleton UI |
| **No empty state guidance** | "No channels found" text has no call-to-action to create or join a channel |
| **[ChannelsPanel](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/client/src/components/layout/panels/ChannelsPanel.jsx#11-516) and [useChannels](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/client/src/hooks/useChannels.js#5-84) use different endpoints** | [ChannelsPanel](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/client/src/components/layout/panels/ChannelsPanel.jsx#11-516) uses `/api/workspaces/:id/channels`; [useChannels](file:///Users/thrishankkuntimaddi/Documents/Chttrix/ChttrixCollab/client/src/hooks/useChannels.js#5-84) hook uses `/api/channels/my?workspaceId=`. Channel data shape is different between the two, making it impossible to share state |

