## 10. FINAL STABILITY SCORE

```
╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║   CHANNEL SYSTEM — STABILITY SCORE                ║
║                                                   ║
║   Backend Logic (Model + Controller + Routes)     ║
║   ████████████░░░░░░░  55 / 100                   ║
║                                                   ║
║   Real-Time Layer (Socket)                        ║
║   █████████░░░░░░░░░░  45 / 100                   ║
║                                                   ║
║   Frontend (UI + State + Service)                 ║
║   ████████░░░░░░░░░░░  40 / 100                   ║
║                                                   ║
║   Security                                        ║
║   ███████░░░░░░░░░░░░  35 / 100                   ║
║                                                   ║
║   Scalability                                     ║
║   ████████░░░░░░░░░░░  40 / 100                   ║
║                                                   ║
║   ─────────────────────────────────────           ║
║   COMPOSITE SCORE        42 / 100                 ║
║                                                   ║
║   STATUS: NOT PRODUCTION-STABLE                   ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
```

**Primary reasons for low score:**

- Two confirmed logic bugs that silently fail without error (assignAdmin guard noop, removeChannelMember filter noop)
- The dual room naming convention means **zero channel-scoped real-time events are delivered to clients today**
- A private channel join bypass exists via `join-via-link`
- The frontend service layer calls four non-existent API endpoints
- N+1 queries on every channel message page load

**The core architecture (JWT auth, schema design, E2EE key lifecycle, RBAC pattern, graceful shutdown) is sound.** The debt is concentrated in a small set of fixable bugs and coordination failures between the legacy and new code paths.
